         <abstract id="aspace_2e8b8558e5f48255602bc53f753d974e">Theodore Hornberger (1906-1975) was
            a professor of English and scholar of Puritanism and Colonial American literature.
            Papers contain lectures, drafts, printed material, reprints, manuscripts, and
            correspondence relating to Hornberger's work on Puritanism and colonial American
            literature. Included are bibliographies compiled by Hornberger on the subjects of
            Puritanism, science, literature, and education, lecture notes on a variety of topics and
            individuals in American literature and history, and a draft manuscript of his book
            Puritanism and Science.</abstract>
