            <scopecontent id="aspace_6174c743fde6d829c9cef6c84d867f86">
               <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
               <p>Largely consists of lectures and lecture notes on a variety of topics and
                  individuals in American literature and history, such as Ralph Waldo Emerson, James
                  Fenimore Cooper, Washington Irving, Cotton Mather, and John Winthrop. Also
                  includes bibliographies Hornberger compiled on the subjects of Puritanism,
                  science, literature, and education, fragments of Hornberger's writings, a
                  manuscript of his book <title type="simple" render="italic">Puritanism and
                     Science</title>, reprints of articles by Hornberger and others, a copy of
                     <title type="simple" render="italic">The Literature of the United
                     States</title> edited by Hornberger and two others, and handwritten notes.</p>
            </scopecontent>
